init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You think it might be a prank, but the phone number is real.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The man on the other end of the phone tells him to meet him at the White House.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A car is then sent to pick him up.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Once Obama arrives at the White House, he's escorted to the Oval Office.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Would you like a drink Mr. President?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Well, I'm just gonna go on and get to the point.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are the only one that can stop them."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "What makes you think I can do this?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: One was red, the other was white.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "What does taking the white pill do?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Obama thought for a few minutes.
